.TH CLUNK 5 
.SH NAME
clunk \- forget about a fid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.ta \w'\fLTclunk 'u
.B
Tclunk	
.IR tag [2]
.IR fid [2]
.br
.B
Rclunk	
.IR tag [2]
.IR fid [2]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B clunk
request informs the file server
that the current file represented by
.I fid 
is no longer needed by the client.
The actual file is not removed on the server.
.PP
Once a fid has been clunked,
the same fid can be reused in a new
.B clone
request.
.PP
Even if the
.B clunk
returns an error, the
.I fid
is no longer valid.
.SH ENTRY POINTS
A
.B clunk
message is generated by
.I close
and indirectly by other actions such as failed
.I open
calls.
